Some have even suggested that people in the commissioner's office have been winking at one another while they make public pronouncements against steroid use. Before the mid-1990s, the substances of choice in the clubhouse were amphetamines and recreational drugs. The prevailing view was that top offensive performances in baseball demanded quick reflexes, good eye-hand coordination, quick feet, flexibility and strong wrists -- not bulky muscles. At the time, many anabolic steroids were illegal if purchased without a prescription. 